MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
Viva La Lassalle!: Veteran actor and stage director Jacques Lassalle has been 
named to head the prestigious French theater company Comedie Francaise. 
He succeeds Antoine Vitez, who died in April. Lassalle, 54, has directed the 
National Theater of Strasbourg since 1983. He said that he would maintain the 
1990-91 program of performances planned by Vitez. GREG BRAXTON 
